included.description:
I was the founding Community Manager for Yelp Miami this means I had the pleasure of being the first brand evangelist to lead a local Yelp community of influencers in Florida. There's no such thing as a "regular" day when you're a Community Manager. My area included Miami-Dade and Broward County. Here are a few ways I filled my days at a wonderful and challenging job:

Procured and maintained sponsors and local partners. I was fortunate to work with some of the best national and local brands in South Florida. 
Developed innovative cross-promotional marketing campaigns. 
Produced events from intimate gatherings of 25 to large-scale events of 700. 
Managed all PR and media relationships. 
Researched and wrote a hyper-local weekly newsletter. 
Hired and managed a small marketing team.
included.title: Senior Marketing and Community Manager

included.summary: I build new technology products and experiences for global users. I've spent a decade working in tech across multiple areas and geographic regions: Research, Strategy, Management, Operations, Marketing, Communities, and International Expansion.
